# 🐳 Keycloak + PostgreSQL Docker Setup (Production-Ready Guide)

---

# 📦 docker-compose.yml (With Full Explanation)

```yaml
version: '3.8'  # Docker Compose version

services:

  # 🐘 PostgreSQL Database Service
  postgres:
    image: postgres:15  # Official PostgreSQL image
    container_name: keycloak-postgres  # Custom container name
    restart: always  # Restart container automatically if it crashes

    environment:
      POSTGRES_DB: ${POSTGRES_DB}  # Default database name
      POSTGRES_USER: ${POSTGRES_USER}  # DB username
      POSTGRES_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}  # DB password

    volumes:
      - postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data  # Persist DB data

    ports:
      - "5432:5432"  # Expose DB port (optional for production)

  # 🔐 Keycloak Authentication Server
  keycloak:
    image: quay.io/keycloak/keycloak:latest  # Official Keycloak image
    container_name: keycloak-server

    command: start-dev  # Dev mode (change in production)

    environment:
      # Database configuration
      KC_DB: postgres
      KC_DB_URL: jdbc:postgresql://postgres:5432/${POSTGRES_DB}
      KC_DB_USERNAME: ${POSTGRES_USER}
      KC_DB_PASSWORD: ${POSTGRES_PASSWORD}

      # Admin credentials
      KEYCLOAK_ADMIN: ${KEYCLOAK_ADMIN}
      KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_PASSWORD: ${KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_PASSWORD}

    ports:
      - "8080:8080"  # Keycloak UI access

    depends_on:
      - postgres  # Ensure DB starts first

volumes:
  postgres_data:  # Named volume for persistence
```

---

# 🔑 .env File (VERY IMPORTANT)

Create a `.env` file in the same folder:

```env
# PostgreSQL Config
POSTGRES_DB=keycloak_db
POSTGRES_USER=keycloak
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=strongpassword

# Keycloak Admin
KEYCLOAK_ADMIN=admin
KEYCLOAK_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123
```

---

# 🚀 How to Run

```bash
docker-compose up -d
```

Open:
👉 [http://localhost:8080](http://localhost:8080)

